Package: shinyformtools
Title: Declarative Database-Backed Shiny Forms
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Georg", "Wiegleb", , "gwiestat@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Build database-backed 'Shiny' form modules from a single
    declarative schema. A form is described once and the package derives the
    database schema, the create, read, update and delete operations, the
    rendering and the 'Shiny' module from that description. Features include
    soft deletion with an audit log and record restore, additive schema
    migrations, database-level uniqueness constraints, configurable table
    views, dynamic and cross-referencing inputs, server-side validation and a
    rights-table permission model. The 'SQLite', 'MariaDB' and 'DuckDB'
    databases are supported behind a common interface.
URL: https://github.com/Gwstat/shinyformtools
BugReports: https://github.com/Gwstat/shinyformtools/issues
